title: For Sale:  Taurus  PT 738FS TCP
postcontent:
Bought less than a week ago brand new. It's still new in box, and has never been fired.  Comes with 1 magazine. Was for my wife, but we found the pink version of the same gun. It is common practice for others on ArmsList to sale guns that they have had issues with such as Failures to feed, Failures to Eject, stovepiping, ect. This one is still new in box and covered under warranty. You'll know it's history...

This is the most current generation of the TCP, i.e., the "E" series. I own the "D" series and carry and shoot it often.

Unlike the Kel Tec P3AT, the Ruger LCP, the DB380, and other .380 ACP pocket pistols in the same price point, the TCP has last round hold open. That is, after you fire the last shot, the slide will stay open making it easier for you to tell when the last shot is fired AND makes it easier and simpler to reload.
